cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is about natural language generation (NLG) in spoken dialogue systems, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which falls under artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG). Hence, cs.AI and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories. The paper proposes a new NLG model that outperforms traditional seq2seq models, which involves optimization and training of neural networks, making cs.NE a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper investigates different generation strategies based on linguistic patterns, which could fall under software development (SD), making it a less likely but still possible sub-category.
